2671.Name: 2018 Colorado State Open
2671.Details:
This year we GIVE BACK! Proceeds from our event will be directed to the Colorado Youth Tennis Foundation.
APTA-sanctioned with Men's and Women's "Open" and "B" categories. 
All teams are guaranteed a minimum of 3 matches.
First round matches will begin Friday, Nov. 30 NO EARLIER than 4pm.
CPTA and APTA membership is required.
2671.RegistrationDetails:
Entry Fee: $170 per team.
CPTA/APTA membership is required in all brackets.If you or your partner are not a member, please be prepared to pay at the tournament desk before your first match. CPTA fee is $70 and includes the APTA fee.
You will be registering you and your partner here.
Men's and Women's Open brackets will be capped at 16 teams.
"B" brackets will be capped at 32 teams.
Please register for this event only if you are available to play throughout Friday evening, all day Saturday and possibly Sunday morning.
2671.Question1: Do you have any food allergies?
2671.Question2: Would you like to donate to the Colorado Youth Tennis Foundation? Donations can be made during the event online or by check.
2671.Question3: Do you have any schedule limitations during the event? Tournament staff will do their best to accommodate, but cannot guarantee

2682.Name: 2019 Colorado State Mixed Doubles Open
2682.Details:
Mixed doubles with "Open" and "B" levels available.
Teams guaranteed at least 3 matches.
Entry fee includes all meals, drinks, favor and prizes.
Proceeds benefit the Colorado Youth Tennis Foundation.
Matches will begin Friday evening no earlier than 5 p.m. continue thru Saturday with finals Saturday night.
Due to time constraints, we estimated the number and sizing of the tournament favor. To ensure you get your size, check in at the tournament desk sooner than later.
2682.RegistrationDetails:
Entry Fee: $130 per team.
 You will be registering you and your partner here.
"Open" bracket will be capped at 16 teams.
"B" brackets will be capped at 32 teams.
Please register for this event only if you are available to play throughout Friday evening, all day Saturday and Saturday night.
2682.Question2: Any schedule requests? We will do our best to accommodate, but no guarantees.
2682.Question3: Would you like information from Pathways Active Travel about vacation opportunities, pricing and discounts via email?
2682.WaiverText:
BY ALLOWING MY NAME TO APPEAR ON Colorado Platform Tennis Association, I and my partner agree to abide by all rules of Colorado Platform Tennis Association . I do hereby and on behalf of myself and my partner, heirs and legal representatives release and forever discharge Colorado Platform Tennis Association of and from any and all claims and demands of every kind, nature and character which I or my partner may have or may hereafter acquire for any and all damages, losses or injuries which may be suffered or sustained by me or my partner. I and my partner also understand that any special medical needs remain the responsibility of the individual player.
I and my partner hereby grant Colorado Platform Tennis Association permission to use our likeness in photograph(s)/video in any and all of its media, publications, whether now known or hereafter existing, controlled by Colorado Platform Tennis Association, in perpetuity, and for other use by Colorado Platform Tennis Association.  I and my partner will make no monetary or other claim against Colorado Platform Tennis Association for the use of such photograph(s)/video.
